# Angular UI Flow Consistency

- Prefer one navigation model per feature: if menu state drives screens, keep event flow explicit and consistent.
- Use typed unions for screen/detail keys and keep `@switch` cases synchronized with those union values.
- For standalone components, every template dependency must be in `@Component.imports` (Material modules, directives, pipes, child standalone components).
- Keep child-to-parent transitions event-driven (`output` + template binding), and avoid wiring save/cancel/search to the same handler unless intentional.
- Reuse shared styles; avoid copy/paste CSS drift across sibling feature folders.
- Keep IDs unique in templates and avoid duplicated static IDs in repeated sections.

## Quick checks before finishing

- `ng build` passes.
- New template bindings map to existing TS properties/methods.
- New component selectors used in templates are imported and standalone-compatible.
